topic.title: Cloning of Zer0Talk with images?
topic.body: It would be nice, if the guy (or girl) who made this site would enable the cloning-feature.

1_1ED3Ho3kmzaKiECtyuqSjDpoE47rKuXeP.body:
> [o4zw5vmpoz5hz78z](#comment_4_1KTjPe9MxoYkcXj78GuZgCcj3R3f3Twh7r): check back in a couple of months :)

Forget it - just a "little kid" whining for his mother.

@oracle: Can't code? Then just f... learn it.
Just want to blog or participate in a forum? You don't have to code anything.
Btw: there is a better way requesting a feature than posting it on a forum not assigned/related to the developer.

> [oracle](#comment_3_1ED3Ho3kmzaKiECtyuqSjDpoE47rKuXeP): I tried to learn to code and I hate it so I stopped trying to learn it. A lot of other people don't want to learn to code as well. Non-coders will not use ZeroNet and your fooling yourself if you think they will. You have to code to add images to your blog and you have to code to change the background color or add buttons or a header bar. I've donated regularly to this project but I will no longer do so till non-coders can use it. I'm also going to discourage other people from using ZeroNet or donating to it, till it's non-coder friendly.

So this is coding for you?
`![something](img/testphoto.png)`
Most forums and blogs using something similar
`[img]http://somesite.com/testphoto.png[/img]`
Sure it would be nice to easyly change the looks of a site without coding anything (i myself just have very basic knowlege of html and css), but for just using a blog or forum it is not neccesary.

> [nofish]: ZeroBlog is just a regular sample site for ZeroNet, it's never meant to be WordPress replacement. If anyone want themes/built-in image editor/meme generator then he will be disappointed, because it's not a planned feature by me, but anyone can clone it and make improvements as it's not related to ZeroNet core development.

So stop complaining and start doing.
